Implementation complete. The solution at `src/game-of-life.ts` uses a sparse representation: a `Set<string>` for living cells and a `Map<string, number>` of neighbor counts built by iterating each living cell's 8 neighbors. Birth/survival rules are applied from those counts. All 12 tests in `src/game-of-life.spec.ts` pass — covering empty input, underpopulation, still life (block), oscillator (blinker), glider, overpopulation, negative coordinates, input immutability, and uniqueness.
